1
00:00:00,146 --> 00:00:01,192
(Previously)
Can I have your number?

2
00:00:01,216 --> 00:00:02,776
So we can stay in touch 24/7 if needed.

3
00:00:04,377 --> 00:00:07,060
Finally, our son's putting
his good looks to good use.

4
00:00:07,143 --> 00:00:08,823
When will you stop being stubborn with me?

5
00:00:09,292 --> 00:00:11,172
I care about you no less
than the vet guy does.

6
00:00:11,532 --> 00:00:12,603
So you're saying,

7
00:00:12,921 --> 00:00:14,561
if I want to give John Wick his medicine,

8
00:00:14,986 --> 00:00:16,393
I should let you pry my mouth open?

9
00:00:16,688 --> 00:00:19,141
Just try to ease into physical touch.

10
00:00:19,781 --> 00:00:21,004
You did really well today.

11
00:00:26,490 --> 00:00:27,594
Here's your Meow Meow Rice.

12
00:00:29,049 --> 00:00:30,049
Enjoy.

13
00:00:33,609 --> 00:00:36,203
Granny Juu, look.

14
00:00:37,468 --> 00:00:41,012
Our café is lively again, just like before.

15
00:00:43,472 --> 00:00:44,272
(I know now.)
(What do you know?)

16
00:00:45,139 --> 00:00:48,203
(I know now that every cat here
appeals to a different target group.)

17
00:00:48,454 --> 00:00:49,454
(What do you mean?)

18
00:00:49,538 --> 00:00:52,194
(Like Jiro, he's the girls' favorite.)

19
00:00:52,842 --> 00:00:55,610
(A tough one like John Wick
is adored by adults.)

20
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:57,770
(Jumbo's Gen Z.)

21
00:00:58,279 --> 00:01:00,012
(So he vibes with the Gen Z customers.)

22
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:05,067
(And for the guys' favorite cat,
that's Jenny, our visual queen.)

23
00:01:05,464 --> 00:01:06,464
As for you, Granny Juu.

24
00:01:06,690 --> 00:01:07,568
Don't be upset.

25
00:01:07,686 --> 00:01:09,578
You'll always be my favorite cat.

26
00:01:09,776 --> 00:01:11,400
Stop hyping your granny.

27
00:01:12,531 --> 00:01:13,813
Take these dishes to the sink.

28
00:01:14,482 --> 00:01:15,524
Customers are waiting.

29
00:01:39,661 --> 00:01:40,661
Do you need a hand?

30
00:01:43,572 --> 00:01:44,572
No, I'm good.

31
00:01:58,632 --> 00:01:59,632
What about you?

32
00:02:00,174 --> 00:02:01,174
Hm?

33
00:02:02,258 --> 00:02:03,795
Which one is your favorite cat?

34
00:02:08,836 --> 00:02:10,318
My favorite cat?

35
00:02:16,009 --> 00:02:17,009
You...

36
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:31,583
wanna guess?

37
00:02:33,197 --> 00:02:34,197
My hint...

38
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:37,208
it's the most stubborn one here.

39
00:02:48,268 --> 00:02:49,407
Aren't all cats stubborn?

40
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,900
"Cat for Cash" (Episode 4)

41
00:03:59,106 --> 00:04:00,106
Excuse me.

42
00:04:00,251 --> 00:04:01,251
Yes?

43
00:04:02,059 --> 00:04:03,615
Can I have a photo?

44
00:04:03,782 --> 00:04:05,001
Sure. If I'd known,

45
00:04:05,121 --> 00:04:08,247
I would've styled my hair.

46
00:04:08,698 --> 00:04:11,638
Uh… I mean a photo of me with Jenny.

47
00:04:12,938 --> 00:04:13,983
Well, never mind.

48
00:04:25,276 --> 00:04:26,525
What was that smile for?

49
00:04:30,204 --> 00:04:31,204
Did you see the notice?

50
00:04:31,392 --> 00:04:32,918
The power will be out this Saturday.

51
00:04:33,012 --> 00:04:34,308
Don't change the subject.

52
00:04:34,511 --> 00:04:36,702
Do you know an F1 racer once hit on me?

53
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,586
Check this out if you don't believe me.

54
00:04:46,907 --> 00:04:48,223
Isn't this AI-generated?

55
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:49,733
I'm telling the truth.

56
00:04:51,116 --> 00:04:54,572
Fine. If you want a picture to fool people,

57
00:04:55,550 --> 00:04:56,827
I'll help.

58
00:05:02,111 --> 00:05:03,111
Is this close enough?

59
00:05:04,382 --> 00:05:05,382
No.

60
00:05:08,321 --> 00:05:09,321
No.

61
00:05:11,966 --> 00:05:13,051
No, don't come any closer.

62
00:05:16,007 --> 00:05:17,225
Where do you want me to send this photo?

63
00:05:17,249 --> 00:05:18,621
Send it straight to the trash bin.

64
00:05:31,302 --> 00:05:32,302
Hey, Lynx.

65
00:05:32,745 --> 00:05:34,107
I found this in front of the café.

66
00:05:34,153 --> 00:05:35,153
Which cat lost it?

67
00:05:36,862 --> 00:05:37,862
Oh.

68
00:05:42,777 --> 00:05:44,805
Come on, Jenny.

69
00:05:44,990 --> 00:05:47,184
You can always let me know
if you want a gift.

70
00:05:51,936 --> 00:05:54,395
(Oppa smells so nice.)

71
00:06:00,499 --> 00:06:01,499
Hey.

72
00:06:01,811 --> 00:06:03,491
Can you clean the litter boxes for me too?

73
00:06:03,762 --> 00:06:04,777
Where are you going?

74
00:06:07,245 --> 00:06:08,623
Can't you tell from my outfit?

75
00:06:09,248 --> 00:06:11,192
I'm going to get my golden body back.

76
00:06:11,601 --> 00:06:13,584
I'll bring you a photo
of a buff trainer too.

77
00:06:17,691 --> 00:06:18,349
Lynx.

78
00:06:18,374 --> 00:06:19,374
Hm?

79
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:23,750
You…

80
00:06:25,768 --> 00:06:27,128
haven't removed the price tag yet.

81
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,500
Having fun?

82
00:06:39,641 --> 00:06:40,641
I'm leaving.

83
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:42,915
(If you like him, just say it.)

84
00:06:43,082 --> 00:06:45,706
(Skip flirting like a teenager.)

85
00:06:49,634 --> 00:06:53,120
I've only heard of mockingbirds.

86
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:55,327
Today, I found a mocking cat.

87
00:06:55,961 --> 00:06:58,622
(Tiger, I don't know
what's wrong with Jenny.)

88
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,502
(She won't eat.)

89
00:07:04,022 --> 00:07:05,022
Jenny,

90
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:07,174
are you okay?

91
00:07:07,376 --> 00:07:08,414
Not feeling well?

92
00:07:09,283 --> 00:07:11,007
(Is she dieting?)

93
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:14,217
(But it might be too late for her age.)

94
00:07:15,262 --> 00:07:16,382
Come on, Jiro.

95
00:07:16,839 --> 00:07:19,756
Look who's flirting here.

96
00:07:19,975 --> 00:07:23,908
(I think you should take her to the vet.)

97
00:07:24,449 --> 00:07:27,711
(She can get treated right away
if something's wrong.)

98
00:07:32,591 --> 00:07:33,591
Good morning, Dr. Pom.

99
00:07:34,995 --> 00:07:35,995
Morning.

100
00:07:37,275 --> 00:07:38,497
Hi there, Jenny.

101
00:07:38,669 --> 00:07:39,669
What's wrong?

102
00:07:39,837 --> 00:07:41,848
She looks down and won't eat.

103
00:07:42,082 --> 00:07:43,610
Could you check her for me?

104
00:07:45,457 --> 00:07:47,398
Let me see, Jenny.

105
00:07:49,368 --> 00:07:51,116
What's wrong?

106
00:07:59,095 --> 00:08:00,301
This collar…

107
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:05,821
With a stain on this spot.

108
00:08:06,366 --> 00:08:07,759
This is really Gong Yoo's collar.

109
00:08:10,722 --> 00:08:11,762
Gong Yoo who?

110
00:08:12,202 --> 00:08:13,309
My new cat.

111
00:08:13,989 --> 00:08:16,197
Ning, could you bring Gong Yoo here?

112
00:08:16,312 --> 00:08:17,312
Sure.

113
00:08:22,610 --> 00:08:23,797
Gong Yoo's here.

114
00:08:24,415 --> 00:08:26,901
There he is. Can't stay still.

115
00:08:27,635 --> 00:08:29,020
Come on. Stay cool.

116
00:08:31,193 --> 00:08:33,298
He snuck out yesterday

117
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,010
and lost his collar.

118
00:08:36,605 --> 00:08:38,313
Beautiful Jenny was the one who found it.

119
00:08:38,713 --> 00:08:40,393
(Thanks a lot, Jenny.)

120
00:08:40,538 --> 00:08:43,032
(You're welcome, Gong Yoo oppa.)

121
00:08:43,183 --> 00:08:45,102
(You're handsome, just like your name.)

122
00:08:47,736 --> 00:08:48,903
Is it just me?

123
00:08:49,213 --> 00:08:51,221
Why does Jenny seem
more energetic now?

124
00:08:52,654 --> 00:08:53,758
No, it's not just you.

125
00:08:54,795 --> 00:08:57,128
I don't think our daughter is sick.

126
00:08:57,769 --> 00:08:59,506
She's just in love.

127
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:01,250
No, that's unlikely.

128
00:09:01,602 --> 00:09:02,605
All the cats have been…

129
00:09:02,999 --> 00:09:04,429
neutered, right?

130
00:09:06,187 --> 00:09:07,187
Wait a minute.

131
00:09:07,839 --> 00:09:09,615
I think…

132
00:09:15,831 --> 00:09:16,831
Yeah, I was right.

133
00:09:17,199 --> 00:09:18,508
If we don't count Jumbo,

134
00:09:18,646 --> 00:09:20,411
Jenny is the only cat who isn't spayed.

135
00:09:21,259 --> 00:09:23,110
Je Meow wanted her to have kittens.

136
00:09:24,216 --> 00:09:27,114
But she hasn't swiped right
on any cat yet.

137
00:09:30,466 --> 00:09:31,727
From what I see,

138
00:09:31,983 --> 00:09:33,313
that wasn't just a swipe right.

139
00:09:33,941 --> 00:09:35,208
She super liked him.

140
00:09:38,229 --> 00:09:41,502
Actually, Gong Yoo's at the age
to start a family too.

141
00:09:44,183 --> 00:09:45,183
Lynx,

142
00:09:47,393 --> 00:09:48,753
should we become one family?

143
00:09:57,407 --> 00:10:00,055
You mean the cats, right?

144
00:10:26,774 --> 00:10:28,395
Come on out.

145
00:10:31,127 --> 00:10:32,127
We're home.

146
00:10:32,296 --> 00:10:33,687
Let's get inside.

147
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:37,802
We're home now.

148
00:10:37,968 --> 00:10:38,768
Let's go.

149
00:10:38,902 --> 00:10:39,902
Hey!

150
00:10:41,734 --> 00:10:42,862
Aren't you going to ask

151
00:10:43,836 --> 00:10:44,836
why I'm mad?

152
00:10:47,499 --> 00:10:48,508
Are you mad at me?

153
00:10:49,745 --> 00:10:50,745
Yeah.

154
00:10:57,336 --> 00:10:59,022
You're trying to
matchmake my daughter.

155
00:10:59,778 --> 00:11:01,538
Have you asked if Dad
is okay with that?

156
00:11:02,556 --> 00:11:05,008
What's wrong with Dr. Pom's cat?

157
00:11:05,281 --> 00:11:08,288
He's handsome,
sweet, and well-bred.

158
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:10,053
And what's wrong
with the cat in this house?

159
00:11:10,808 --> 00:11:11,808
Isn't it "him"

160
00:11:12,239 --> 00:11:14,159
that's always by your side
during the hard times?

161
00:11:16,537 --> 00:11:19,333
Are you still talking about cats?

162
00:11:21,939 --> 00:11:22,939
Yeah.

163
00:11:23,715 --> 00:11:24,908
You really don't get it.

164
00:11:26,626 --> 00:11:27,626
I'm leaving then.

165
00:11:46,314 --> 00:11:47,314
Let's get inside.

166
00:11:50,612 --> 00:11:53,803
So someone's hitting on your crush.

167
00:11:56,504 --> 00:11:57,610
Yeah, Pa.

168
00:11:59,007 --> 00:12:01,623
And my crush goes along with it.

169
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:07,821
Did you confess
your feelings to your crush?

170
00:12:11,229 --> 00:12:12,480
Huh, no.

171
00:12:13,812 --> 00:12:16,422
You're going to wait
until you get a wedding invitation?

172
00:12:20,402 --> 00:12:22,217
I'm just not that person's type.

173
00:12:24,091 --> 00:12:30,115
That person like warm, kind guys,
with a medical degree on the wall.

174
00:12:32,375 --> 00:12:36,318
Warm? I don't think
you are second to anyone.

175
00:12:37,851 --> 00:12:40,806
You even cried watching The Tiger King.

176
00:12:42,548 --> 00:12:43,701
Why would you bring that up?

177
00:12:45,298 --> 00:12:46,409
It's gonna be alright.

178
00:12:46,981 --> 00:12:48,725
There's still tomorrow to try again.

179
00:12:51,443 --> 00:12:52,443
Cheers.

180
00:12:59,538 --> 00:13:00,599
Try again tomorrow.

181
00:13:00,765 --> 00:13:01,765
Thanks, Pa.

182
00:13:37,994 --> 00:13:40,639
What? My Jenny is in love?

183
00:13:42,175 --> 00:13:44,909
Yeah. With Dr. Pom's
Korean-style oppa cat.

184
00:13:45,105 --> 00:13:45,989
His name's Gong Yoo.

185
00:13:46,056 --> 00:13:47,056
Gong Yoo?

186
00:13:48,659 --> 00:13:51,397
My legs are shaking,
and it's not a K-pop dance move.

187
00:13:51,754 --> 00:13:53,480
It's the reaction to having
my heart broken.

188
00:13:54,202 --> 00:13:55,508
Hang in there.

189
00:13:56,954 --> 00:13:57,954
It's okay.

190
00:13:58,805 --> 00:14:00,909
If Jenny really chooses that oppa,

191
00:14:01,437 --> 00:14:04,637
this "Oppor" will step aside.

192
00:14:07,339 --> 00:14:13,013
I'd rather be nice guy alone,
than be someone bad without you.

193
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:08,039
You'll catch a cold, you silly thing.

194
00:15:09,985 --> 00:15:10,989
What's gotten into you?

195
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:12,745
You're giving me goosebumps.

196
00:15:13,636 --> 00:15:15,378
You just saw me in microwave mode.

197
00:15:20,717 --> 00:15:21,923
If you're changing modes,

198
00:15:22,835 --> 00:15:24,106
change your smoking habit too.

199
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:26,097
Cats hate the smell of cigarettes.

200
00:15:31,823 --> 00:15:32,823
Lynx.

201
00:15:33,351 --> 00:15:34,618
Hi, Dr. Pom.

202
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:38,106
I was just out running around here
with Gong Yoo.

203
00:15:38,728 --> 00:15:41,591
Is it okay if I come in
for a cup of coffee?

204
00:15:42,707 --> 00:15:43,707
Absolutely.

205
00:16:09,312 --> 00:16:11,113
That's the one, Gong Yoo.

206
00:16:12,716 --> 00:16:14,303
The cat who stole Jenny's heart.

207
00:16:14,842 --> 00:16:19,073
(His face screams
"Gong Tek" more. Right, folks?)

208
00:16:19,162 --> 00:16:22,118
(Wow, he still has his balls.)

209
00:16:22,293 --> 00:16:25,338
(Bro Jiro's got none left,
but a big belly.)

210
00:16:25,438 --> 00:16:26,438
(Butt out!)

211
00:16:26,573 --> 00:16:31,708
(Granny Juu, tell Jenny
not to judge a cat by its fur.)

212
00:16:31,991 --> 00:16:36,360
(Eotteoke, shinja, gwenchanayo…)

213
00:16:36,524 --> 00:16:38,722
(What, Granny?
(How could you fall for him too?)

214
00:16:39,017 --> 00:16:42,791
(John Wick, my bro.
(I've only got you left. Help me.)

215
00:16:42,858 --> 00:16:45,639
(Just accept it. That's all I can say.)

216
00:16:45,762 --> 00:16:47,494
(What a useless bunch
of furballs you all are.)

217
00:16:47,518 --> 00:16:49,438
(Guess this coach
has to handle it himself then.)

218
00:16:49,534 --> 00:16:50,547
(Let's go, Tiger.)

219
00:16:54,134 --> 00:16:55,266
What are you talking about?

220
00:16:56,528 --> 00:16:59,826
I'm asking Dr. Pom to tell me
about Gong Yoo.

221
00:17:04,605 --> 00:17:07,246
These days, if you
want to know someone,

222
00:17:08,265 --> 00:17:10,110
you start with their parents.

223
00:17:13,461 --> 00:17:14,909
So, what were you like as a kid?

224
00:17:16,980 --> 00:17:19,926
Well… just like any kid.

225
00:17:20,579 --> 00:17:25,066
I'm a straight-A student
with some honors.

226
00:17:28,521 --> 00:17:30,915
Whoa. Total nerd.

227
00:17:32,246 --> 00:17:36,606
Me, I was a school track star.

228
00:17:37,416 --> 00:17:40,791
A teacher spotted my talent
while I was chasing my enemy.

229
00:17:41,636 --> 00:17:43,203
He even jumped on a truck.

230
00:17:44,149 --> 00:17:45,311
But I still caught up to him.

231
00:17:47,434 --> 00:17:49,009
Is that something
you should brag about?

232
00:17:49,793 --> 00:17:53,010
Alright, I'll talk about my son then.

233
00:17:53,536 --> 00:17:57,426
This son of mine used to be in
a Michelin-star restaurant.

234
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:01,320
All high-class, VVIP customers
played with his belly.

235
00:18:03,293 --> 00:18:04,420
What about your son?

236
00:18:04,986 --> 00:18:06,498
Has he ever received such treatment?

237
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:08,213
My son can't compare.

238
00:18:08,726 --> 00:18:11,699
Gong Yoo used to belong to
a Korean teacher who worked here.

239
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:14,513
But the teacher got transferred
to the countryside

240
00:18:15,067 --> 00:18:19,306
and couldn't keep him,
so I had to take him in.

241
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:22,426
Oh, just like Jenny's story.

242
00:18:23,187 --> 00:18:26,713
Her original owner was a beauty blogger
who used Jenny to boost sales.

243
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,693
When sales dropped,

244
00:18:29,059 --> 00:18:31,339
they just abandoned Jenny
and replaced her with a new cat.

245
00:18:31,973 --> 00:18:35,393
They both got abandoned,
no wonder they hit it off.

246
00:18:39,813 --> 00:18:42,806
(What? Am I wrong to be born
with a silver spoon in my mouth?)

247
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:45,426
(You all love drama, right?)

248
00:18:45,613 --> 00:18:47,820
(Here comes some refreshment!)

249
00:18:49,267 --> 00:18:50,267
Watch out!

250
00:18:51,483 --> 00:18:52,483
Are you okay, Dr. Pom?

251
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:53,436
Don't worry about it.

252
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:54,470
Your shirt got wet.

253
00:18:54,596 --> 00:18:56,232
Come upstairs.
I'll lend you some clothes.

254
00:18:56,256 --> 00:18:57,256
You'll catch a cold.

255
00:18:57,677 --> 00:18:59,117
Guess I'll have to trouble you then.

256
00:19:02,483 --> 00:19:03,848
Stay here for a sec, Gong Yoo.

257
00:19:12,883 --> 00:19:14,823
Jiro, look.

258
00:19:15,123 --> 00:19:16,733
That vet dude now gets
to be in Lynx's room.

259
00:19:16,757 --> 00:19:21,396
(What? I went from silver spoon cat to
filthy scapegoat just like that?)

260
00:19:24,656 --> 00:19:26,503
I only have small-sized clothes.

261
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:28,303
I don't think they'll fit you.

262
00:19:32,976 --> 00:19:34,932
What about that one?
I think I can wear it.

263
00:19:35,149 --> 00:19:38,423
Ah, that one isn't mine.

264
00:19:39,603 --> 00:19:40,603
Whose is it then?

265
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:42,503
It's Tiger's.

266
00:19:43,035 --> 00:19:45,598
He stayed over the other night.
I haven't returned it to him yet.

267
00:19:47,083 --> 00:19:48,116
Stayed over?

268
00:19:48,623 --> 00:19:51,516
Well, he was here
to help with the cats.

269
00:19:51,923 --> 00:19:55,843
And actually, we're coworkers…

270
00:19:57,603 --> 00:19:59,616
in theory.

271
00:20:01,697 --> 00:20:02,823
And in practice?

272
00:20:05,563 --> 00:20:07,396
I'm starting to wonder…

273
00:20:07,937 --> 00:20:10,756
he might...

274
00:20:11,437 --> 00:20:12,510
and I mean "might"...

275
00:20:14,496 --> 00:20:15,563
have a crush on me.

276
00:20:15,890 --> 00:20:16,890
I knew it!

277
00:20:17,230 --> 00:20:19,956
That's why something felt off.

278
00:20:20,503 --> 00:20:22,123
He's trying to hit on my little brother.

279
00:20:22,883 --> 00:20:24,636
I'm still not sure.

280
00:20:26,556 --> 00:20:28,923
Do you have a way to test it?

281
00:20:50,463 --> 00:20:51,463
It's just…

282
00:20:52,350 --> 00:20:53,716
you were gone for a while,

283
00:20:54,510 --> 00:20:56,990
so I was worried about you.

284
00:20:58,117 --> 00:20:59,117
Ah.

285
00:20:59,537 --> 00:21:03,390
I took some time picking out a shirt.

286
00:21:04,023 --> 00:21:05,403
It was hard to find one I liked.

287
00:21:07,669 --> 00:21:12,210
Looks like we have the same taste.

288
00:21:13,332 --> 00:21:14,350
Hey, Lynx.

289
00:21:14,803 --> 00:21:16,096
Are you free this Monday?

290
00:21:17,223 --> 00:21:20,143
No plans. What's up?

291
00:21:20,713 --> 00:21:21,513
Want to go on a date?

292
00:21:21,574 --> 00:21:22,574
No!

293
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:25,950
I mean…

294
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:28,010
no worries about the cats.

295
00:21:28,590 --> 00:21:29,600
I'll take care of them.

296
00:21:32,566 --> 00:21:34,726
I want you to take Jenny
to go on a date with Gong Yoo,

297
00:21:34,843 --> 00:21:35,903
so they can get closer.

298
00:21:38,103 --> 00:21:41,003
Sure. Let's go on a date on Monday.

299
00:21:41,676 --> 00:21:42,676
Okay, deal.

300
00:21:55,969 --> 00:21:56,969
Dr. Pom.

301
00:21:59,917 --> 00:22:02,330
Are you sure this will work?

302
00:22:02,810 --> 00:22:03,810
Trust me.

303
00:22:03,916 --> 00:22:06,523
If Tiger really has feelings for you,
he'll definitely show up.

304
00:22:08,017 --> 00:22:09,017
Dr. Pom, look.

305
00:22:10,787 --> 00:22:11,787
Who's this?

306
00:22:12,349 --> 00:22:13,503
He's in every photo.

307
00:22:13,736 --> 00:22:15,853
Wearing sunglasses, probably a stalker.

308
00:22:15,950 --> 00:22:17,290
So scary. Who's this?

309
00:22:17,997 --> 00:22:18,997
I'm sorry.

310
00:22:23,736 --> 00:22:26,216
I didn't realize I was in the frame.

311
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,003
What are you doing here?

312
00:22:28,309 --> 00:22:30,309
I brought Jiro out for a walk.

313
00:22:31,157 --> 00:22:32,157
What a coincidence, huh?

314
00:22:33,183 --> 00:22:34,183
Right, Jiro?

315
00:22:40,723 --> 00:22:44,110
Seriously, it's just a walk with a cat.

316
00:22:44,896 --> 00:22:46,410
Do you really need to dress up?

317
00:22:48,317 --> 00:22:49,396
This is my usual look.

318
00:22:50,656 --> 00:22:53,610
You've only seen me in casual clothes
and my café uniform.

319
00:22:54,589 --> 00:22:55,909
You're probably not used to this.

320
00:22:56,496 --> 00:22:57,496
Lynx.

321
00:22:57,877 --> 00:22:59,316
Us pushing this cart together,

322
00:22:59,383 --> 00:23:01,790
we kind of look like
dads pushing a baby stroller, don't we?

323
00:23:02,657 --> 00:23:03,657
We do.

324
00:23:05,896 --> 00:23:09,296
Jenny, you get to go out like this.

325
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:11,893
Sitting in a stroller
must be pretty boring, huh?

326
00:23:12,263 --> 00:23:13,543
Cats aren't like dogs.

327
00:23:14,169 --> 00:23:16,473
They prefer sitting still and
watching what's around them.

328
00:23:17,523 --> 00:23:20,336
Then why did we bring them here?

329
00:23:22,043 --> 00:23:26,546
To widen their world,
and to make some fresh content.

330
00:23:33,577 --> 00:23:36,337
Nice weather like this is perfect for
taking new photos of our babies.

331
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:40,823
Speaking of taking photos,
I came prepared too.

332
00:23:44,660 --> 00:23:46,500
Here's a trick to get more likes
in cat photos.

333
00:23:46,662 --> 00:23:48,315
You need to shoot at their eye level.

334
00:23:49,766 --> 00:23:50,766
Gong Yoo, come on.

335
00:23:52,460 --> 00:23:56,600
If they avoid looking at the camera,
use cat treats or toys to lure them.

336
00:23:56,661 --> 00:23:57,661
Gong Yoo, dear.

337
00:24:05,587 --> 00:24:06,695
(You done yet?)

338
00:24:06,834 --> 00:24:09,274
(I've been holding this smile
so long my gums are drying out.)

339
00:24:12,822 --> 00:24:15,006
Do you want a photo of you with them?

340
00:24:15,378 --> 00:24:17,924
Nah, I'm good. It's a hassle.

341
00:24:18,873 --> 00:24:20,606
There's research that says

342
00:24:20,910 --> 00:24:24,293
posting photos with a cat
makes you look warm and kind.

343
00:24:25,069 --> 00:24:26,094
More importantly…

344
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:30,372
It raises your chances of
getting hit on by 23.5%.

345
00:24:36,034 --> 00:24:38,798
Well then… since we're already here.

346
00:24:40,162 --> 00:24:41,814
A few photos won't hurt.

347
00:24:43,328 --> 00:24:46,416
Keep holding Jenny in your arms
and pat her head.

348
00:24:46,742 --> 00:24:48,222
I'll make it look like a candid shot.

349
00:24:49,109 --> 00:24:50,109
Okay.

350
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:52,120
Jenny.

351
00:24:53,254 --> 00:24:54,520
Very cute.

352
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:56,702
Look.

353
00:24:57,126 --> 00:24:58,921
Wow. It's really good.

354
00:25:00,278 --> 00:25:01,704
Can I post it on my Stories?

355
00:25:01,946 --> 00:25:02,946
Mm.

356
00:25:04,630 --> 00:25:06,320
I think the composition's still off.

357
00:25:07,350 --> 00:25:09,110
It's not following the rule of thirds.

358
00:25:11,325 --> 00:25:12,969
Before you start using
photography jargon,

359
00:25:13,124 --> 00:25:14,764
how about learning
how to use that camera?

360
00:25:16,043 --> 00:25:17,493
Would you like to try it too, Tiger?

361
00:25:18,530 --> 00:25:19,722
Then let Lynx choose.

362
00:25:20,318 --> 00:25:22,002
Whose photo will he choose
for his Stories?

363
00:25:24,224 --> 00:25:25,224
Sounds good.

364
00:25:26,174 --> 00:25:29,100
I want to see who Lynx will choose too.

365
00:25:45,810 --> 00:25:47,620
It's okay. I can do it myself.

366
00:25:49,030 --> 00:25:50,030
Let me.

367
00:26:24,075 --> 00:26:25,081
Can you smile?

368
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:34,800
I am smiling.

369
00:26:37,275 --> 00:26:38,619
Relax a little, Lynx.

370
00:26:39,498 --> 00:26:40,498
Think of it like

371
00:26:40,759 --> 00:26:42,959
you're using this photo
to charm people on social media.

372
00:26:46,804 --> 00:26:47,804
Okay, Dr. Pom.

373
00:26:48,526 --> 00:26:49,526
Ready?

374
00:27:15,767 --> 00:27:16,917
Are you done shooting?

375
00:27:24,433 --> 00:27:25,512
Alright. I'm done.

376
00:27:26,104 --> 00:27:28,112
(So bored~ I'm outta here.)

377
00:27:28,185 --> 00:27:29,185
Jiro!

378
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:30,790
Jiro!

379
00:27:43,462 --> 00:27:44,462
Alright, judge.

380
00:27:45,107 --> 00:27:46,604
Whose photo are you choosing?

381
00:27:53,501 --> 00:27:56,600
Tiger is good at snapping your photo too.

382
00:27:58,133 --> 00:27:59,311
It could be a fluke.

383
00:28:00,483 --> 00:28:02,203
How much more do you want
to see to believe?

384
00:28:03,217 --> 00:28:07,413
I guess I…

385
00:28:08,981 --> 00:28:11,109
want to hear it clearly from his own lips.

386
00:28:14,366 --> 00:28:16,020
But where is he now?

387
00:28:19,612 --> 00:28:20,709
I'm calling him.

388
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:32,001
He left it there?

389
00:28:35,429 --> 00:28:36,429
You said…

390
00:28:37,088 --> 00:28:38,610
you wanted to hear from him, right?

391
00:28:40,513 --> 00:28:41,513
Yeah, why?

392
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:44,876
MY FAVORITE CAT

393
00:28:44,919 --> 00:28:47,703
You know how cats in heat
give off a special scent

394
00:28:48,096 --> 00:28:50,716
to let their potential mates know?

395
00:28:51,161 --> 00:28:52,223
I think…

396
00:28:53,174 --> 00:28:54,600
maybe you could try copying cats.

397
00:29:19,561 --> 00:29:21,126
I WISH I COULD READ YOUR HEART

398
00:29:31,264 --> 00:29:34,007
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT TO HEAR IT?

399
00:29:57,331 --> 00:29:58,331
I think…

400
00:29:59,236 --> 00:30:00,711
maybe you could try copying cats.

401
00:30:01,129 --> 00:30:02,627
How, Dr. Pom?

402
00:30:04,634 --> 00:30:08,592
Try switching up your usual perfume.

403
00:30:09,283 --> 00:30:13,318
Only the favorite cat near you
will know when your scent changes.

404
00:30:17,811 --> 00:30:18,811
Okay.

405
00:31:19,458 --> 00:31:21,103
Aren't you going to work yet?

406
00:31:23,855 --> 00:31:24,855
Huh?

407
00:31:29,286 --> 00:31:30,416
What do I do, Pa?

408
00:31:32,179 --> 00:31:34,821
Seems like I'm losing my crush at work
to that Pom-eranian dude.

409
00:31:37,471 --> 00:31:39,909
And what breed is your crush at the café?

410
00:31:40,235 --> 00:31:41,235
Persian.

411
00:31:44,585 --> 00:31:45,641
Wait, how did you know?

412
00:31:48,185 --> 00:31:49,640
I asked Dong.

413
00:31:50,076 --> 00:31:54,409
So I know you didn't open a lounge,
but a cat café.

414
00:31:55,888 --> 00:31:57,515
Sorry for not telling you.

415
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,524
I just didn't want you to worry.

416
00:31:59,882 --> 00:32:02,826
You know cats are bad for your health.

417
00:32:03,832 --> 00:32:05,312
Why are you still obsessed with them?

418
00:32:05,343 --> 00:32:06,877
But my favorite cat…

419
00:32:09,661 --> 00:32:10,801
is the owner of that café.

420
00:32:12,098 --> 00:32:13,218
Je Meow's kid?

421
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:18,768
Didn't Je Meow have…

422
00:32:19,678 --> 00:32:20,678
a son?

423
00:32:23,087 --> 00:32:24,087
So what?

424
00:32:25,859 --> 00:32:27,018
Are you going to stop me?

425
00:32:44,065 --> 00:32:45,065
Fine.

426
00:32:46,021 --> 00:32:47,515
As my son,

427
00:32:49,012 --> 00:32:50,230
you're not allowed to give up.

428
00:32:53,907 --> 00:32:56,722
You know when I went after your mom?

429
00:32:58,449 --> 00:33:00,607
A hundred guys were chasing her too.

430
00:33:01,492 --> 00:33:04,416
But I managed to win her heart.

431
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:12,724
But my rival is a cat doctor.

432
00:33:15,850 --> 00:33:17,086
So what if he's a cat doctor?

433
00:33:17,474 --> 00:33:18,610
Come on. Don't forget this.

434
00:33:19,865 --> 00:33:22,189
Your dad is Singha Bangsue.

435
00:33:22,921 --> 00:33:25,111
The most feared creditor in the area.

436
00:33:30,470 --> 00:33:31,470
That's true, Pa.

437
00:33:32,095 --> 00:33:33,526
Mark my words.

438
00:33:34,636 --> 00:33:38,507
This Tiger will crush that
Pom-eranian doc into pieces.

439
00:33:44,717 --> 00:33:47,557
About you opening a cat café,

440
00:33:48,984 --> 00:33:50,318
don't let your mom know yet.

441
00:33:51,091 --> 00:33:55,358
Otherwise, we'll both
get torn to pieces.

442
00:34:42,825 --> 00:34:43,825
Lynx.

443
00:34:51,027 --> 00:34:52,718
The power company's cutting power today.

444
00:34:58,371 --> 00:34:59,371
Yes, I know.

445
00:35:04,312 --> 00:35:05,312
Lynx!

446
00:35:09,908 --> 00:35:11,026
It's gonna be okay, Jenny.

447
00:35:11,171 --> 00:35:14,294
Don't you cry or pout,
This rebound guy will help you out!

448
00:35:14,719 --> 00:35:16,604
- Forget that player.
- Hold on, Krapor.

449
00:35:17,041 --> 00:35:18,041
What's going on?

450
00:35:18,652 --> 00:35:21,324
I ran into Dr. Pom at the market.

451
00:35:22,088 --> 00:35:25,918
He said the original owner
wanted Gong Yoo back today.

452
00:35:26,342 --> 00:35:29,240
I thought you and Tiger knew.

453
00:35:33,459 --> 00:35:35,623
Don't be sad, sweetie.

454
00:35:36,302 --> 00:35:38,324
Dad will find you someone ten times hotter.

455
00:35:38,882 --> 00:35:41,082
(No one can replace my Gong Yoo.)

456
00:35:44,721 --> 00:35:47,808
(Yeah, no one can replace Gong Yoo.)

457
00:35:48,329 --> 00:35:50,016
(So go say goodbye to him.)

458
00:35:50,132 --> 00:35:53,824
(What's the point?
(He has to leave anyway.)

459
00:35:54,090 --> 00:35:59,107
(I know how much it hurts to keep your
feelings inside well.)

460
00:35:59,653 --> 00:36:00,653
(Go say goodbye.)

461
00:36:01,516 --> 00:36:03,705
(So you won't end up
crying later like I did.)

462
00:36:05,903 --> 00:36:07,583
Hey, how is she doing?

463
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:12,842
Lynx, close the café for a day.

464
00:36:17,004 --> 00:36:18,924
Let's bring our daughter
to confess her feelings.

465
00:36:24,295 --> 00:36:26,293
Krapor said
Gong You is leaving around noon.

466
00:36:28,775 --> 00:36:29,809
Hold tight, Jenny.

467
00:36:31,140 --> 00:36:32,699
Shit. Whose car is it?

468
00:36:32,784 --> 00:36:34,310
It's okay. Let me take care of it.

469
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:45,421
Damn it. It's not moving.

470
00:36:45,587 --> 00:36:46,909
The handbrake's on.

471
00:36:47,085 --> 00:36:48,290
What else can we do?

472
00:36:48,393 --> 00:36:49,626
Want me to smash the window?

473
00:36:49,765 --> 00:36:50,905
Whose damn car is this?

474
00:36:51,075 --> 00:36:52,907
This is inconsiderate
as hell. What an idiot.

475
00:36:53,147 --> 00:36:54,557
I'm so pissed right now.

476
00:36:54,578 --> 00:36:57,258
Don't let me find out who parked like this.
I swear I'll punch them.

477
00:36:57,340 --> 00:36:58,340
What a jerk.

478
00:36:59,044 --> 00:37:00,105
What do we do now?

479
00:37:00,838 --> 00:37:02,021
Whose damn car is this?

480
00:37:07,342 --> 00:37:08,342
We've got no time left.

481
00:37:09,926 --> 00:37:11,926
Hell with it. For my daughter!

482
00:37:17,673 --> 00:37:18,683
No one's answering.

483
00:37:19,450 --> 00:37:20,830
The clinic's just ahead.

484
00:37:21,380 --> 00:37:22,380
We're almost there.

485
00:37:25,233 --> 00:37:26,233
Ouch.

486
00:37:27,207 --> 00:37:28,207
Lynx.

487
00:37:28,268 --> 00:37:29,268
You okay?

488
00:37:30,787 --> 00:37:31,787
I'm okay.

489
00:37:35,221 --> 00:37:36,310
It's gonna be too late.

490
00:37:36,789 --> 00:37:37,789
Take care of Jiro for me.

491
00:37:37,832 --> 00:37:38,832
What about you?

492
00:37:39,380 --> 00:37:41,410
I'll show you that I never lie.

493
00:38:02,413 --> 00:38:03,413
Let's go.

494
00:38:09,261 --> 00:38:10,061
Doc!

495
00:38:10,283 --> 00:38:11,283
Doc, wait!

496
00:38:15,849 --> 00:38:16,849
Is everything alright?

497
00:38:16,919 --> 00:38:18,198
Do you have a minute?

498
00:38:18,956 --> 00:38:20,773
I'm bringing Jenny
to say goodbye to Gong Yoo.

499
00:38:27,790 --> 00:38:29,186
Sorry for not telling you earlier.

500
00:38:29,484 --> 00:38:31,800
The original owner just found a place
that allows pets.

501
00:38:31,926 --> 00:38:34,600
They have to leave soon,
so I need to bring Gong Yoo to them now.

502
00:38:37,302 --> 00:38:39,717
(I thought I didn't get
the chance to say goodbye to you.)

503
00:38:39,893 --> 00:38:44,507
(Congrats. They changed their mind
and want you back.)

504
00:38:44,616 --> 00:38:48,181
(In my case, they didn't even
bother to come looking for me.)

505
00:38:48,424 --> 00:38:51,621
(Since then, I've been scared
to open my heart again.)

506
00:38:51,912 --> 00:38:53,412
(Then I met you.)

507
00:38:54,218 --> 00:38:57,718
(During those brief times we had together,
I was so happy.)

508
00:38:58,296 --> 00:38:59,425
(I…)

509
00:39:00,153 --> 00:39:01,408
(I like you.)

510
00:39:01,820 --> 00:39:03,306
(I'm sorry, Jenny)

511
00:39:03,476 --> 00:39:05,709
(But I only see you as a little sister.)

512
00:39:06,242 --> 00:39:07,400
(Gong Yoo oppa.)

513
00:39:08,714 --> 00:39:09,727
(Thank you, though.)

514
00:39:09,836 --> 00:39:13,512
(That's okay. Good luck… big brother.)

515
00:39:13,726 --> 00:39:15,052
(Take care of yourself.)

516
00:39:17,433 --> 00:39:18,433
I have to go now.

517
00:39:19,524 --> 00:39:21,712
Okay. Thank you so much.

518
00:39:24,561 --> 00:39:25,761
Bye-bye, Jenny.

519
00:39:26,001 --> 00:39:27,995
I'll ask them to bring
Gong Yoo to visit sometime.

520
00:39:29,656 --> 00:39:30,656
See you.

521
00:39:37,264 --> 00:39:40,915
I think our daughter's just got rejected.

522
00:39:41,303 --> 00:39:43,921
Yeah, I can tell that too.

523
00:39:45,626 --> 00:39:46,918
It's alright, Jenny.

524
00:39:47,420 --> 00:39:48,992
You are pretty and strong.

525
00:39:49,402 --> 00:39:50,602
You don't need a partner.

526
00:39:51,837 --> 00:39:53,924
(You were so brave to say it out.)

527
00:39:54,263 --> 00:39:56,919
(I could never do that, you know?)

528
00:39:57,013 --> 00:39:58,604
(Thank you, Jiro.)

529
00:40:00,204 --> 00:40:01,724
Since we closed the café today,

530
00:40:02,161 --> 00:40:03,426
let's take a new set of photos.

531
00:40:03,873 --> 00:40:05,413
Don't make the cats blurry this time.

532
00:40:06,140 --> 00:40:07,220
Got it.

533
00:40:07,593 --> 00:40:10,720
This time, I'll take
better photos than Dr. Pom.

534
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:14,360
Let's go.

535
00:40:22,286 --> 00:40:23,920
We're home, Jiro.

536
00:40:26,693 --> 00:40:29,333
It's good to take cats out
for fresh air once in a while, isn't it?

537
00:40:30,346 --> 00:40:31,346
How about this,

538
00:40:31,587 --> 00:40:33,806
next week, whichever cats behave

539
00:40:34,106 --> 00:40:35,993
get two free field trip tickets.

540
00:40:36,986 --> 00:40:38,506
Does that sound good, Jiro?

541
00:40:40,987 --> 00:40:42,893
Alright, let me take
the cats to their room.

542
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,120
You're home, kids.

543
00:40:47,767 --> 00:40:48,767
Alright, Jenny.

544
00:40:52,373 --> 00:40:53,373
Jiro.

545
00:41:12,391 --> 00:41:13,391
Lynx!

546
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:16,120
Lynx.

547
00:41:17,826 --> 00:41:18,866
Are you okay?

548
00:41:23,393 --> 00:41:24,640
Watch out for the broken glass.

549
00:41:25,207 --> 00:41:26,259
I'm coming right now.

550
00:41:26,667 --> 00:41:27,787
Are you a cat?

551
00:41:28,246 --> 00:41:29,819
How can you see in the dark like this?

552
00:41:45,006 --> 00:41:46,006
You okay, right?

553
00:41:47,159 --> 00:41:48,413
How do you know where I am?

554
00:41:52,166 --> 00:41:53,613
Though I cannot see anything,

555
00:41:55,826 --> 00:41:56,906
I can smell.

556
00:42:11,287 --> 00:42:12,627
Why did you change your perfume?

557
00:42:13,847 --> 00:42:15,206
I like the old one more.

558
00:42:18,147 --> 00:42:19,153
What about you?

559
00:42:19,953 --> 00:42:21,706
You don't smell like cigarettes anymore.

560
00:42:42,433 --> 00:42:43,433
Lynx.

561
00:42:48,279 --> 00:42:50,979
You used to ask me…

562
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:57,133
which one is my favorite cat, right?

563
00:43:06,973 --> 00:43:07,973
You…

564
00:43:11,873 --> 00:43:13,320
You are my favorite cat.

565
00:43:24,447 --> 00:43:25,666
Let's go on a date next week.

566
00:43:44,070 --> 00:43:46,153
(Next Episode)
My name's Leo. I'm your brother.

567
00:43:46,873 --> 00:43:48,082
I was thinking of moving in here instead.

568
00:43:48,106 --> 00:43:49,847
You should start making good memories
with your brother too.

569
00:43:49,871 --> 00:43:50,616
I'm not sure about that.

570
00:43:50,637 --> 00:43:53,100
Look at all the cats in the café.
You managed to tame them all.

571
00:43:53,124 --> 00:43:55,003
I haven't even tamed the latest one yet.

572
00:43:55,080 --> 00:43:56,242
And now there's another one.

573
00:43:56,319 --> 00:43:57,616
You two seem close.

574
00:43:57,721 --> 00:43:58,521
Are you dating?
No.

575
00:43:59,275 --> 00:44:01,907
Since you two aren't together yet,
can I flirt with him?

576
00:44:02,270 --> 00:44:03,990
If you're afraid of losing to your brother,

577
00:44:04,195 --> 00:44:05,250
how about we start dating?
